  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Comprehensive Response for the Volcan de Fuego Emergency</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM plans to support the Government of Guatemala through a people-centred approach that considers diverse age/gender needs. This initiative will be a part of inter-agency shelter coordination, to support local sectoral learning and identification of best practices, deficient at this stage, and will focus on these main areas: 1. Officialregistration of individuals in collective centres: Develop and establishan integrated registration system to provide registration for identification, family reunification, humanitarian assistance, and security purposes; 2. Data collection through the DTM system to support humanitarian assistance and coordination: Tracking numbers of people by age/sex and identifying the critical needs within the clusters structures to improve humanitarian aid and plan for stabilization and reintegration; and 3. Upgrade shelters and sites for comprehensive and integrated management, improvement, and logistics in collective centres.Improve site and shelter management by conducting shelter assessments and planning, organizing and managing teams, delivering assistance, and improving existing or building new infrastructure, based on data collected and assessments conducted through this project.</narrative>
  </description>
